    "This is immediate since whenever f ∈ Lip b and π j ∈ Lip are such that one of π j 's is constant on a neighbourhood of spt f, then T i (f, π 1,..., π d) = 0 for every i.",
    "Hence also T (f, π 1,..., π d) = 0.",
    "Remark 3.15.Several interesting open questions concerning the functional-analytic structure of the introduced spaces arise.",
